[10.10.2009, contest entry] http://coderack.org/

About

The *Rack::Codehighlighter* is a middleware which
allows for easy connecting a code highlighter of somebody's choice
to an HTML page containing pieces of programming code.
Parameters to *Rack::Codehighlighter* are: the name of a highlighter
and a specification of how to find the pieces of code in the page.


Usage

For example, to colorize code in *pre* elements with well known
*coderay* highlighter use the following:

    require 'coderay'
    use Rack::Codehighlighter, 
      :coderay, :element => "pre", 
      :pattern => /\A:::(\w+)\s*\n/

The first parenthesized expression from the pattern /\A:::(\w+)\s*\n/ 
will be used to match the language name. 
For example, from the *pre* element below the *ruby* name 
will be extracted

    <pre>:::ruby
    printf "hello world"
    </pre>

and the *coderay* Ruby scanner will be used to highlight the second line.

The code below implements three most popular Ruby code highlighters
of today: *coderay*, *syntax* and *ultraviolet*. 

